1
00:00:06,574 --> 00:00:08,274
Thank you.

2
00:00:08,342 --> 00:00:10,109
I can't believe
you remember that.

3
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:11,344
What, are you kidding me?

4
00:00:11,412 --> 00:00:12,913
You singing
"Everybody Hurts."

5
00:00:12,980 --> 00:00:14,047
Jules:
Oh sorry.

6
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:15,682
Yeah, my R.E.M phase.

7
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:17,083
(Chuckles)

8
00:00:17,151 --> 00:00:19,452
Well, I couldn't take
my eyes off you, so...

9
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,087
Are you sure it didn't have
anything to do

10
00:00:21,155 --> 00:00:22,588
with what I was wearing
maybe?

11
00:00:22,656 --> 00:00:25,758
Uh, black leather miniskirt,
white tank top...

12
00:00:25,825 --> 00:00:27,593
Seriously though,
you guys were good.

13
00:00:27,661 --> 00:00:28,594
You coulda went
on the road.

14
00:00:28,662 --> 00:00:30,262
I don't think so.

15
00:00:30,329 --> 00:00:32,631
Yeah,
I got a confession.

16
00:00:33,567 --> 00:00:34,767
Your best show -

17
00:00:34,834 --> 00:00:36,702
five am,
morning after graduation,

18
00:00:36,770 --> 00:00:38,836
on the roof
of the gym.

19
00:00:38,904 --> 00:00:40,271
What?

20
00:00:40,338 --> 00:00:41,739
You just got dumped
by Curtis

21
00:00:41,807 --> 00:00:45,043
at that party...

22
00:00:45,110 --> 00:00:46,544
Oh God,
I don't believe this.

23
00:00:46,612 --> 00:00:47,946
You took your guitar,
you went up to roof

24
00:00:48,013 --> 00:00:50,815
and you came up
with this...

25
00:00:50,883 --> 00:00:52,183
Really gentle song-

26
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:53,384
you were up there?

27
00:00:53,452 --> 00:00:54,751
I'm sorry.

28
00:00:54,819 --> 00:00:57,654
It's just after I heard that
I thought...

29
00:00:57,722 --> 00:01:00,123
I felt like I knew you.

30
00:01:01,059 --> 00:01:03,126
You know there's this
wine tasting thing,

31
00:01:03,194 --> 00:01:04,795
Niagara on the lake,
next weekend.

32
00:01:04,862 --> 00:01:07,030
<i>I was thinking, you know,</i>
<i>maybe we could go.</i>

33
00:01:07,098 --> 00:01:08,565
Um...

34
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:10,133
I mean we don't have
to stay over,

35
00:01:10,201 --> 00:01:11,734
it could just be
a day trip.

36
00:01:11,802 --> 00:01:12,635
I was just thinking 'cause
we've been seeing each other

37
00:01:12,703 --> 00:01:12,868
for a while.

38
00:01:15,672 --> 00:01:16,806
I... I just-

39
00:01:16,873 --> 00:01:18,407
(loud pop nearby,
someone screams)

40
00:01:18,475 --> 00:01:19,408
What was that?

41
00:01:19,476 --> 00:01:20,275
That was gunfire.

42
00:01:20,343 --> 00:01:21,777
(Screaming nearby)

43
00:01:21,845 --> 00:01:23,079
Steve:
Hold on.

44
00:01:23,146 --> 00:01:24,546
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Steve, wait!</i>

45
00:01:24,615 --> 00:01:25,547
(Car tires and brakes screech)
Steve: Hey watch!

46
00:01:25,616 --> 00:01:26,848
(Tires screech,
horns honk)

47
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:27,983
Jules:
Stop!

48
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,253
Man:
Somebody's been shot.

49
00:01:32,321 --> 00:01:33,688
Jules:
Winnie, it's Jules.

50
00:01:33,756 --> 00:01:35,023
Oh hey, how are you enjoying
your day off?

51
00:01:35,091 --> 00:01:36,591
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>I've got shots fired.</i>

52
00:01:36,659 --> 00:01:40,294
Inside the Sultan Grill
on the Danforth.

53
00:01:40,362 --> 00:01:41,730
Guys! Guys!

54
00:01:41,797 --> 00:01:43,196
Sam: What's happening?
Winnie: Are you okay?

55
00:01:43,264 --> 00:01:44,498
We're outside the restaurant
right now.

56
00:01:44,565 --> 00:01:46,100
Is the shooter still inside?

57
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:47,601
I can't see.

58
00:01:48,536 --> 00:01:50,237
Someone's shot, Jules.
I gotta get in there.

59
00:01:50,304 --> 00:01:51,471
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>No, Steve, we need to wait</i>
<i>for backup.</i>

60
00:01:51,539 --> 00:01:53,007
<i>The shooter might</i>
<i>still be active.</i>

61
00:01:53,074 --> 00:01:54,474
Sam:
Jules, hang tight!
We're coming!

62
00:01:54,542 --> 00:01:56,209
Team one, hot call!
Suit up!

63
00:01:56,277 --> 00:01:57,377
He may be dead
before they get here.

64
00:01:57,445 --> 00:01:58,746
Jules:
You don't go in there.

65
00:01:58,813 --> 00:02:00,480
<i>Steve!</i>

66
00:02:00,548 --> 00:02:01,981
<i>Winnie:</i>
<i>Shots fired at the Sultan Grill</i>
<i>on the Danforth.</i>

67
00:02:02,049 --> 00:02:04,117
<i>There's one confirmed</i>
<i>victim down.</i>

68
00:02:04,185 --> 00:02:05,918
<i>Gunman:</i>
<i>I warned you!</i>

69
00:02:05,986 --> 00:02:07,187
<i>I ask you a simple question,</i>
<i>all you have to do is answer.</i>

70
00:02:07,255 --> 00:02:08,855
Waitress: Eric...
Gunman: Now one more time!

71
00:02:08,922 --> 00:02:10,423
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa,
tell me where he is!

72
00:02:10,491 --> 00:02:12,159
I don't know!

73
00:02:14,762 --> 00:02:15,927
Where's Riyaz?

74
00:02:15,995 --> 00:02:17,296
I'm sorry,
I don't know who that is.

75
00:02:17,364 --> 00:02:19,398
Where are your hands?
Where are your hands?!

76
00:02:19,466 --> 00:02:20,832
No, no cell phones.

77
00:02:21,768 --> 00:02:23,101
Hey, all cell phones
on the floor now.

78
00:02:23,170 --> 00:02:24,970
Now! Go get 'em!
Collect them!

79
00:02:25,905 --> 00:02:27,239
<i>Now!</i>

80
00:02:28,074 --> 00:02:29,408
Anyone caught attempting
to communicate with him

81
00:02:29,476 --> 00:02:30,809
will be shot.

82
00:02:30,877 --> 00:02:31,742
Do you understand me?!
It's gonna be okay.

83
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:33,444
Total communication blackout.

84
00:02:33,512 --> 00:02:34,712
<i>Steve:</i>
<i>I'm a medic,</i>
<i>I'm gonna help you.</i>

85
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:35,913
<i>You're gonna be okay.</i>

86
00:02:35,981 --> 00:02:37,582
All right.
Hey-hey-hey-hey-hey!

87
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:38,949
<i>What're you doing?</i>

88
00:02:39,017 --> 00:02:40,084
He just wants to make sure
that he's okay.

89
00:02:40,152 --> 00:02:41,919
Okay, well get away.
Come on get away.

90
00:02:41,987 --> 00:02:43,754
Get away from him!

91
00:02:43,822 --> 00:02:45,623
You, lock it.

92
00:02:45,691 --> 00:02:46,957
Lock the door!

93
00:02:47,025 --> 00:02:48,292
You, barricade it -
tables and chairs.

94
00:02:48,359 --> 00:02:49,859
<i>Come on!</i>

95
00:02:49,927 --> 00:02:51,895
Nobody's leaving
until I get some answers.

96
00:02:51,962 --> 00:02:53,863
All right.
Okay.

97
00:02:53,931 --> 00:02:56,333
You - knives, forks, uh...

98
00:02:56,401 --> 00:02:57,867
Corkscrews,
any sharp implements.

99
00:02:57,935 --> 00:02:59,836
If I find anything
that can be used as a weapon...

100
00:02:59,904 --> 00:03:01,205
Go!

101
00:03:01,272 --> 00:03:03,839
Come on, come on, come on!

102
00:03:03,907 --> 00:03:06,342
That's good.
Get against the wall.

103
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:07,443
Hands where I can see 'em.

104
00:03:07,511 --> 00:03:08,578
Go! Move!

105
00:03:11,515 --> 00:03:12,748
(SUV's rumble up)

106
00:03:18,388 --> 00:03:19,654
Set up a perimeter.

107
00:03:19,722 --> 00:03:21,223
Get the uniforms
to keep these people back.

108
00:03:21,290 --> 00:03:22,857
<i>Let's do it now.</i>

109
00:03:22,925 --> 00:03:24,025
Parker:
We're dealing with at least
one shooter.

110
00:03:24,093 --> 00:03:26,194
Wordy:
How many hostages?

111
00:03:26,262 --> 00:03:27,195
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Ten, maybe more.</i>

112
00:03:27,263 --> 00:03:28,162
<i>Sam:</i>
<i>Jules?</i>

113
00:03:28,231 --> 00:03:29,531
Limited vantage.

114
00:03:29,599 --> 00:03:31,065
Looks like the front doors
are barricaded.

115
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:33,435
Maybe Jules can feed us
information from inside.

116
00:03:33,502 --> 00:03:35,769
Sam:
No, if that gunman finds out
Jules is a cop...

117
00:03:39,608 --> 00:03:40,641
All right.

118
00:03:40,709 --> 00:03:41,975
Hey, quiet!
Hey, hey!

119
00:03:42,043 --> 00:03:43,477
You guys clear outta here!

120
00:03:43,545 --> 00:03:44,778
Go!

121
00:03:44,846 --> 00:03:47,414
I want everyone to keep quiet,
I gotta think.

122
00:03:47,482 --> 00:03:49,082
You, on the floor.

123
00:03:49,150 --> 00:03:50,884
<i>Knees. Here.</i>

124
00:03:50,952 --> 00:03:52,852
Hands behind the head.

125
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:54,721
You know what this place is,
right?

126
00:03:54,788 --> 00:03:56,289
It's, it's a restaurant.

127
00:03:56,357 --> 00:03:58,458
Yes.
Yes, yes, yes, yes.

128
00:03:58,525 --> 00:04:01,361
It looks very much like
a restaurant, but do you...

129
00:04:01,428 --> 00:04:04,597
(Exasperated exhale)
Do you know what it is?

130
00:04:04,665 --> 00:04:06,031
(Exhales forcefully)

131
00:04:06,099 --> 00:04:08,768
What're you looking at?!

132
00:04:08,835 --> 00:04:09,802
<i>You know what</i>
<i>it's really for?</i>

133
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:11,570
(Jules' phone buzzes)

134
00:04:11,638 --> 00:04:14,173
<i>Gunman:</i>
<i>You know who eats here</i>
<i>and what they want?</i>

135
00:04:14,241 --> 00:04:15,307
<i>Huh?!</i>

136
00:04:16,676 --> 00:04:18,677
<i>Where's Riyaz?!</i>

137
00:04:18,745 --> 00:04:19,945
(Parker's PDA beeps)

138
00:04:20,013 --> 00:04:21,313
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Jules is okay.</i>

139
00:04:21,381 --> 00:04:23,448
She says there's one gunman,
18 hostages.

140
00:04:23,516 --> 00:04:25,216
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>What does the gunman want?</i>

141
00:04:25,284 --> 00:04:27,152
<i>Gunman:</i>
<i>Riyaz should be here now.</i>

142
00:04:27,219 --> 00:04:28,753
<i>Where is he?</i>

143
00:04:28,821 --> 00:04:29,921
(PDA beeps)

144
00:04:29,989 --> 00:04:31,156
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Looking for Riyaz.</i>

145
00:04:31,223 --> 00:04:32,490
Who's Riyaz?

146
00:04:32,557 --> 00:04:34,125
<i>Hey, Spike,</i>

147
00:04:34,193 --> 00:04:35,960
<i>see if there's a connection</i>
<i>between the Sultan Grill</i>

148
00:04:36,028 --> 00:04:38,462
<i>and someone named Riyaz.</i>

149
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:39,863
On it.

150
00:04:39,931 --> 00:04:41,298
You told him not to come
because I'm here,

151
00:04:41,365 --> 00:04:43,400
didn't you?
I don't even know who you mean.

152
00:04:43,467 --> 00:04:45,335
I gotta try to talk to him.

153
00:04:45,403 --> 00:04:47,070
Woman:
(Frightened gasp)

154
00:04:48,339 --> 00:04:49,273
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Sir?</i>

155
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:50,373
Hey, you stay
where you are.

156
00:04:50,441 --> 00:04:51,374
I'm gonna stay
right here.

157
00:04:51,442 --> 00:04:52,642
All right, good.

158
00:04:52,710 --> 00:04:54,577
My name's Jules.
What's your?

159
00:04:54,645 --> 00:04:54,812
Oh... (Laughs)

160
00:04:57,004 --> 00:04:59,238
You're looking for somebody
named Riyaz?

161
00:04:59,306 --> 00:05:00,306
Yeah, what,
you know him?

162
00:05:00,374 --> 00:05:01,575
No, I don't.

163
00:05:01,642 --> 00:05:02,776
But maybe I could help you
find him.

164
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:05,345
Oh well, he knows him.

165
00:05:05,412 --> 00:05:07,380
And if he had just told me
where he was when I asked,

166
00:05:07,448 --> 00:05:08,982
then this wouldn't have
happened.

167
00:05:09,049 --> 00:05:10,583
(Sirens blip and wail)

168
00:05:10,650 --> 00:05:12,317
No, oh no.

169
00:05:12,385 --> 00:05:13,819
(Panicking)
No, no, okay...

170
00:05:13,887 --> 00:05:15,654
Uh, everybody...

171
00:05:15,722 --> 00:05:17,790
Go! Go!
Everybody against the door!

172
00:05:17,858 --> 00:05:20,459
<i>Uh, go to the front.</i>
<i>Everybody, go, go, go!</i>

173
00:05:20,527 --> 00:05:21,694
Get to the front.

174
00:05:21,761 --> 00:05:23,696
Go. Get to the front.

175
00:05:23,763 --> 00:05:25,563
Go now!

176
00:05:25,631 --> 00:05:28,299
He's lining up hostages
against the window.

177
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:30,067
He's making a human shield.

178
00:05:30,135 --> 00:05:31,569
Sam?

179
00:05:31,637 --> 00:05:33,705
No vantage.
I'm coming down.

180
00:05:33,772 --> 00:05:35,072
Hey, hey,
what're you doing?

181
00:05:35,140 --> 00:05:36,440
Sir, this man is losing
a lot of blood.

182
00:05:36,509 --> 00:05:37,876
He needs to go
to the hospital.

183
00:05:37,943 --> 00:05:39,644
I said no one's leaving.

184
00:05:39,712 --> 00:05:40,311
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Okay, well this is my friend,</i>
<i>Steve.</i>

185
00:05:40,379 --> 00:05:41,845
He's a paramedic.

186
00:05:41,913 --> 00:05:42,880
<i>If you let him look at him,</i>
<i>maybe he can help him</i>

187
00:05:42,947 --> 00:05:44,548
and then you can find Riyaz.

188
00:05:44,616 --> 00:05:45,782
<i>That's what you want,</i>
<i>right?</i>

189
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:47,050
(Laboured breaths)

190
00:05:47,986 --> 00:05:49,052
Yeah.

191
00:05:52,089 --> 00:05:54,591
Just hang in there, buddy,
hang in.

192
00:05:55,527 --> 00:05:56,693
Okay,
he's barely conscious.

193
00:05:56,761 --> 00:05:57,827
Look, I'm gonna need
some napkins,

194
00:05:57,895 --> 00:05:59,461
clean water
and plastic wrap.

195
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,330
I can get them.

196
00:06:02,432 --> 00:06:03,933
Okay, go.

197
00:06:04,968 --> 00:06:06,468
<i>Stay where I can see you.</i>

198
00:06:06,537 --> 00:06:08,004
Come on, come on.

199
00:06:08,071 --> 00:06:09,471
Move fast!

200
00:06:11,207 --> 00:06:12,909
Okay, we know who
we're looking for.

201
00:06:12,976 --> 00:06:16,045
The owner of the restaurant
is Riyaz Fayad.

202
00:06:16,112 --> 00:06:18,180
Parker:
Good, now let's find out
who's got a beef with him.

203
00:06:18,248 --> 00:06:20,849
<i>Neighbours,</i>
<i>disgruntled employees.</i>

204
00:06:20,917 --> 00:06:22,617
What's going on, Eddie?

205
00:06:22,685 --> 00:06:23,919
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>All right, we got an air vent</i>
<i>on the roof.</i>

206
00:06:23,986 --> 00:06:25,820
Might be able to feed
a snake cam through that.

207
00:06:25,888 --> 00:06:27,356
All right, go for it.
Let's do it.

208
00:06:30,926 --> 00:06:33,428
Is Eric gonna be okay?

209
00:06:33,495 --> 00:06:35,229
He's got decreased breath
sounds on the left side.

210
00:06:35,297 --> 00:06:36,397
What does that mean?

211
00:06:36,465 --> 00:06:37,398
His lung collapsed.

212
00:06:37,466 --> 00:06:38,666
Oh my God.

213
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,401
Look, he needs chest
decompression.

214
00:06:40,469 --> 00:06:42,403
Wouldn't happen to have a kit
in your purse, do you?

215
00:06:42,471 --> 00:06:43,704
Can you improvise?

216
00:06:43,772 --> 00:06:45,940
Yeah, but I need a pen,
I need some vodka...

217
00:06:46,007 --> 00:06:46,973
A knife.

218
00:06:47,041 --> 00:06:48,108
Sir?

219
00:06:49,577 --> 00:06:51,078
A knife.

220
00:06:51,145 --> 00:06:52,312
What do you think I am?
An idiot?

221
00:06:52,380 --> 00:06:53,680
Sir, I promise.
We're gonna hand it back

222
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:56,516
as soon as we're done,
please.

223
00:06:57,452 --> 00:06:59,018
All right.

224
00:06:59,087 --> 00:07:00,653
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Whoa, whoa,</i>
<i>what're you doing?</i>

225
00:07:00,721 --> 00:07:02,721
You try anything,

226
00:07:04,091 --> 00:07:05,657
I'm gonna shoot her.

227
00:07:08,562 --> 00:07:10,963
Waitress:
(Whimpers and cries)

228
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:12,298
I'm gonna get the vodka.

229
00:07:12,365 --> 00:07:13,966
Gunman:
Okay, go.

230
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:16,935
Gunman: Just go!
Jules: I'm going.

231
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:30,215
(Approaching footsteps)

232
00:07:30,282 --> 00:07:32,350
Jules: Here you go.
Steve: Thanks.

233
00:07:33,952 --> 00:07:35,152
Steve:
Okay, the knife.

234
00:07:35,220 --> 00:07:36,453
Jules:
Mm-hmm.

235
00:07:38,923 --> 00:07:39,856
You got it?

236
00:07:39,924 --> 00:07:41,191
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

237
00:07:41,259 --> 00:07:43,360
Look, I'm sorry
for getting us into this.

238
00:07:43,428 --> 00:07:45,996
You were just trying
to help.

239
00:07:46,931 --> 00:07:47,998
Okay.

240
00:07:49,634 --> 00:07:50,699
(Grunt of effort)

241
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:54,470
Oh my God.

242
00:07:58,609 --> 00:07:59,542
Okay, hand me the pen.

243
00:07:59,610 --> 00:08:00,676
Okay.

244
00:08:11,086 --> 00:08:12,320
(Motor buzzes)

245
00:08:13,289 --> 00:08:14,222
<i>Steve:</i>
<i>Hand me the plastic bag.</i>

246
00:08:14,290 --> 00:08:15,957
Yeah.

247
00:08:16,725 --> 00:08:17,692
<i>Steve:</i>
