00:16:50,540 --> 00:16:52,207
<i>When he got out,</i>

484
00:16:52,275 --> 00:16:55,310
I tried to get him
to come home, but...

485
00:16:55,378 --> 00:16:56,945
He didn't want any part of me.

486
00:16:57,012 --> 00:16:59,281
Okay, where's he living now?
Do you know?

487
00:16:59,349 --> 00:17:01,349
Robert:
He's, uh, at Harmony House.

488
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:04,552
It's a group home.
St. George Street.

489
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:06,587
Okay, just hang on one second,
Mr. Lagosto.

490
00:17:06,655 --> 00:17:07,821
Get a hold of Harmony House.

491
00:17:07,889 --> 00:17:09,022
I'm sure he's got
a social worker there.

492
00:17:09,090 --> 00:17:10,358
Let's get in touch
with him.

493
00:17:13,395 --> 00:17:15,162
Parker: Mr. Irwin?
Clive: Yeah.

494
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:16,397
How're you doing?
I'm sergeant Parker.

495
00:17:16,465 --> 00:17:17,597
Thank you for coming.

496
00:17:17,665 --> 00:17:20,333
Will you follow me
please, sir?

497
00:17:20,401 --> 00:17:22,569
So you're Davis's
primary social worker?

498
00:17:22,637 --> 00:17:24,738
Yeah, I've known him
for over two years.

499
00:17:24,805 --> 00:17:25,872
Look,
this is all my fault.

500
00:17:25,939 --> 00:17:27,307
Davis is my responsibility.

501
00:17:27,375 --> 00:17:29,709
Look, we understand
that Davis has been charged

502
00:17:29,777 --> 00:17:30,910
with assault in the past.

503
00:17:30,978 --> 00:17:32,279
Now,
these violent outbursts,

504
00:17:32,346 --> 00:17:33,545
do they happen often?

505
00:17:33,613 --> 00:17:35,547
He's not some kind of monster.
He's sick.

506
00:17:35,615 --> 00:17:37,015
Yeah, I understand that,
Mr. Irwin.

507
00:17:37,083 --> 00:17:39,485
Look, paranoid schizophrenics
are prone to suspicion.

508
00:17:39,552 --> 00:17:40,819
If they feel threatened,

509
00:17:40,887 --> 00:17:42,554
they sometimes lash out
to protect themselves.

510
00:17:42,622 --> 00:17:43,889
But Davis believes
that terrorists

511
00:17:43,956 --> 00:17:45,891
are planning an attack
on the city.

512
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,559
What did he say?

513
00:17:47,627 --> 00:17:49,794
He said that restaurant
is a front for a terror cell.

514
00:17:50,962 --> 00:17:53,230
Has he mentioned
Riyaz Fayad before?

515
00:17:53,299 --> 00:17:54,666
I don't think so,

516
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:57,101
but he's been talking a lot
about terrorists lately.

517
00:17:57,169 --> 00:17:58,936
Do you know what might have
triggered that?

518
00:17:59,004 --> 00:18:01,406
Terrorism's all over the news
these days.

519
00:18:01,473 --> 00:18:04,241
Bombings in Madrid,
Chechnya...

520
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:05,375
Yeah.

521
00:18:07,412 --> 00:18:08,478
Eric?

522
00:18:11,816 --> 00:18:13,149
<i>Waitress:</i>
<i>Oh my God!</i>

523
00:18:13,217 --> 00:18:14,551
What's happening?

524
00:18:14,619 --> 00:18:17,487
His pulse is thready.
There's no breath sounds.

525
00:18:17,555 --> 00:18:18,855
Angela:
Oh my God.

526
00:18:18,923 --> 00:18:21,090
Come on, Eric,
hang in there!

527
00:18:21,158 --> 00:18:22,758
<i>Come on, buddy.</i>

528
00:18:23,694 --> 00:18:25,862
<i>Hang in there, buddy.</i>

529
00:18:25,930 --> 00:18:27,163
Steve.

530
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:29,532
<i>Waitress:</i>
<i>Why're you stopping?</i>

531
00:18:29,599 --> 00:18:31,267
Help, please!

532
00:18:31,335 --> 00:18:32,902
Tell him to keep going.

533
00:18:32,970 --> 00:18:35,271
<i>Why're you stopping?!</i>

534
00:18:35,339 --> 00:18:36,873
I'm sorry, it's...

535
00:18:36,941 --> 00:18:37,973
No!

536
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:40,309
Man: Oh my God.
Davis: Hey!

537
00:18:40,376 --> 00:18:41,877
Is he dead?

538
00:18:41,945 --> 00:18:43,411
Yes.

539
00:18:43,479 --> 00:18:44,546
Oh.

540
00:18:45,481 --> 00:18:46,648
Oh?

541
00:18:46,716 --> 00:18:48,050
Okay, Angela...

542
00:18:48,117 --> 00:18:49,952
That's all
you have to say?!

543
00:18:50,019 --> 00:18:51,954
<i>Eric never did anything</i>
<i>to you.</i>

544
00:18:52,021 --> 00:18:53,155
<i>Davis:</i>
<i>Okay, shhh.</i>

545
00:18:53,223 --> 00:18:54,688
He harboured
a known terrorist.

546
00:18:54,756 --> 00:18:57,391
Riyaz is not a terrorist!
What's wrong with you?!

547
00:18:57,459 --> 00:18:58,860
Okay, she's escalating him now.

548
00:18:58,927 --> 00:19:00,061
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Angela, you know what?</i>

549
00:19:00,128 --> 00:19:01,729
We need to stay really calm
right now.

550
00:19:01,796 --> 00:19:04,265
<i>Davis:</i>
<i>Hey! All right, just shut up!</i>
<i>Quiet!</i>

551
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:05,499
<i>Shut up!</i>
<i>Both of you!</i>

552
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:07,601
You come in here
on a Muslim witch hunt...

553
00:19:07,669 --> 00:19:09,303
No, you're not listening to me,
all right?

554
00:19:09,371 --> 00:19:11,504
This is a front
for a terrorist operation.

555
00:19:11,572 --> 00:19:12,572
You are not listening to me.

556
00:19:12,639 --> 00:19:13,974
So then what does that
make me?

557
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:16,542
All right, oh my God,
you're one of them.

558
00:19:16,610 --> 00:19:18,245
You're a black widow.

559
00:19:18,312 --> 00:19:20,247
So now I'm a terrorist too?!

560
00:19:20,314 --> 00:19:21,915
Aw crap!

561
00:19:21,983 --> 00:19:23,449
Davis:
Everybody, get back!
Stay back, everybody!

562
00:19:23,517 --> 00:19:24,851
<i>Get back! Get back!</i>

563
00:19:24,919 --> 00:19:26,585
Davis, what do you see?

564
00:19:26,652 --> 00:19:27,686
All right, she's got a bomb.
She's about to detonate a bomb.

565
00:19:27,754 --> 00:19:29,088
Angela:
We're all terrorists!

566
00:19:29,155 --> 00:19:31,123
Get down!
She's got a bomb!

567
00:19:31,191 --> 00:19:32,224
All right.

568
00:19:32,292 --> 00:19:33,625
Hey.

569
00:19:33,693 --> 00:19:35,094
(Gunshot pops)

570
00:19:35,161 --> 00:19:36,528
Shots fired!

571
00:19:36,596 --> 00:19:37,662
Davis: Why'd you do that?
Jules: Are you okay?

572
00:19:37,730 --> 00:19:40,299
I think so.

573
00:19:40,599 --> 00:19:41,867
Oh my gosh!
Steve?

574
00:19:44,789 --> 00:19:47,098
It's Steve.
He's been shot.

575
00:19:50,893 --> 00:19:52,127
Steve.

576
00:19:52,195 --> 00:19:53,128
I'm okay.

577
00:19:53,196 --> 00:19:55,130
Just lay still,
Angela.

578
00:19:55,198 --> 00:19:56,765
<i>Sam:</i>
<i>Jules needs backup,</i>
<i>I wanna go in.</i>

579
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:58,167
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>From where?</i>

580
00:19:58,234 --> 00:19:59,969
This back door leads
right into the basement.

581
00:20:00,036 --> 00:20:01,803
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Okay. Sam?</i>

582
00:20:01,871 --> 00:20:03,304
You're just covering on this,
all right?

583
00:20:03,372 --> 00:20:04,472
She knows what she's doing.

584
00:20:04,539 --> 00:20:06,774
I know she does.

585
00:20:06,842 --> 00:20:08,576
Just saying.

586
00:20:08,643 --> 00:20:09,710
Yes, sir.

587
00:20:12,948 --> 00:20:14,849
Jules:
We gotta stop the bleeding.

588
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:16,184
Steve:
(Low pained grunts)

589
00:20:16,251 --> 00:20:18,452
It's okay.
I got it, I got it.

590
00:20:20,254 --> 00:20:22,622
Get back, get back!
Get back!

591
00:20:23,557 --> 00:20:24,491
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>All right, let's slow down.</i>

592
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:25,925
Shut up! Shut up!

593
00:20:25,994 --> 00:20:27,861
Hands above your head!

594
00:20:27,928 --> 00:20:29,463
Hands above your head!

595
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,964
All right, I know that
you're afraid right now, Davis.

596
00:20:31,032 --> 00:20:32,299
All right,
we have to find something

597
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:33,400
<i>to bind her hands and feet.</i>

598
00:20:33,468 --> 00:20:34,433
<i>We have to dismantle the bomb.</i>

599
00:20:34,501 --> 00:20:35,834
She's not gonna hurt you.

600
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:37,603
She's got a bomb!
Are you blind?!

601
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:39,038
Patron:
Oh my God.

602
00:20:39,106 --> 00:20:40,539
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>He's turning on Jules.</i>

603
00:20:40,607 --> 00:20:42,674
We gotta find a way
to get past his delusions.

604
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:43,742
He said we needed soldiers here.

605
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:45,277
Maybe I can talk to him as one.

606
00:20:45,345 --> 00:20:47,079
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Go for it, Sam.</i>

607
00:20:47,147 --> 00:20:48,347
But, boss, this place has serious
security for a restaurant;

608
00:20:48,415 --> 00:20:49,882
<i>I'm looking</i>
<i>at reinforced steel.</i>

609
00:20:49,949 --> 00:20:52,083
After 9-11, a lot
of middle eastern businesses

610
00:20:52,151 --> 00:20:53,585
have been targets for vandals.

611
00:20:53,653 --> 00:20:55,220
I'm gonna have
to torch my way through.

612
00:20:55,287 --> 00:20:57,322
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Copy that.</i>

613
00:20:58,625 --> 00:21:01,393
Riyaz:
This brick was thrown
through our window.

614
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:02,861
(Reading)
Die Arab pig.

615
00:21:02,929 --> 00:21:04,630
Sayid was in the room
when it happened.

616
00:21:04,697 --> 00:21:06,697
<i>He was terrified.</i>

617
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:08,799
Go back
to the middle east.

618
00:21:08,867 --> 00:21:10,167
He was born in Vancouver.

619
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:12,937
Why didn't you report this?

620
00:21:13,005 --> 00:21:14,471
You think anyone cares
about death threats

621
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:17,107
against a suspected
terrorist?

622
00:21:17,175 --> 00:21:19,577
Why were you accused
in the first place?

623
00:21:19,645 --> 00:21:21,879
Back in, uh... 2004,

624
00:21:23,748 --> 00:21:26,082
I started donating money
to an Islamic charity.

625
00:21:26,150 --> 00:21:28,751
I was told
it was a scholarship fund

626
00:21:28,818 --> 00:21:30,118
for underprivileged kids.

627
00:21:30,186 --> 00:21:33,656
I found out later that
the charity was a front

628
00:21:33,723 --> 00:21:35,658
used to fund
terrorist activities,

629
00:21:35,725 --> 00:21:37,125
including the London bombings.

630
00:21:37,193 --> 00:21:39,261
And from that they assumed
you were the leader

631
00:21:39,328 --> 00:21:40,596
of a terrorist cell?

632
00:21:40,664 --> 00:21:42,264
I convinced a lot of other
members of my mosque

633
00:21:42,331 --> 00:21:44,732
to donate
to the same charity.

634
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,935
We thought we were doing
something good.

635
00:21:47,002 --> 00:21:50,672
ATU dragged us from our homes
in the middle of the night.

636
00:21:50,739 --> 00:21:52,774
<i>They interrogated us</i>
<i>for hours.</i>

637
00:21:52,841 --> 00:21:55,376
They froze our bank accounts,
confiscated our passports...

638
00:21:55,444 --> 00:21:56,711
Once it got leaked
to the press,

639
00:21:56,779 --> 00:21:58,846
that's when all the threats
started to happen.

640
00:21:58,914 --> 00:22:00,481
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>Hey, Ed?</i>

641
00:22:00,549 --> 00:22:01,949
<i>Just got off the phone</i>
<i>with the anti-terror unit.</i>

642
00:22:02,016 --> 00:22:04,350
Excuse me one second.

643
00:22:05,419 --> 00:22:06,720
Any intel
on a possible attack?

644
00:22:06,788 --> 00:22:08,221
No. And they checked
with other agencies -

645
00:22:08,289 --> 00:22:09,556
no chatter, nothing.

646
00:22:09,624 --> 00:22:11,324
And Mr. Fayad?

647
00:22:11,392 --> 00:22:12,659
Spike:
Well, he's gonna be on
a no-fly list for a while,

648
00:22:12,727 --> 00:22:14,260
but they're wrapping up
their investigation.

649
00:22:14,328 --> 00:22:15,896
He's been cleared
of any wrongdoing.

650
00:22:15,964 --> 00:22:17,529
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Okay, good to know.</i>
<i>Thanks, Spike.</i>

651
00:22:20,233 --> 00:22:21,533
The ATU is clearing you.

652
00:22:21,602 --> 00:22:22,635
What?

653
00:22:22,703 --> 00:22:23,636
Really?

654
00:22:23,704 --> 00:22:25,004
Oh my God.

655
00:22:25,072 --> 00:22:27,372
Oh my God! It's over!
(Elated laughter)

656
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,541
Hey, Spike,
a lot of these email threats

657
00:22:29,610 --> 00:22:33,444
<i>are being sent from the same</i>
<i>I.P. address.</i>

658
00:22:33,512 --> 00:22:34,846
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>I'll run a trace,</i>

659
00:22:34,914 --> 00:22:36,047
<i>see if we can connect them</i>
<i>to Davis.</i>

660
00:22:50,128 --> 00:22:52,029
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>All right, I'm just gonna</i>
<i>change this, okay?</i>

661
00:22:52,097 --> 00:22:54,364
Don't try to be the tough guy.
I know what it feels like.

662
00:22:54,432 --> 00:22:56,767
I've been shot before.
I know how much pain you're in.

663
00:22:56,835 --> 00:22:58,702
So, how do you like the date
so far?

664
00:22:58,770 --> 00:23:01,138
You really know how to keep
a girl on her toes, huh?

665
00:23:01,205 --> 00:23:03,007
Wait 'til you see what...
Ungh!

666
00:23:03,074 --> 00:23:04,341
I have planned
for the next one.

667
00:23:06,410 --> 00:23:07,977
Woman:
We can't. He's just gonna
start shooting again.

668
00:23:08,045 --> 00:23:09,479
Man:
That's why we gotta do it fast.
Disarm him.

669
00:23:09,547 --> 00:23:11,681
Woman 2:
There are a lot of us
and only one of him.

670
00:23:11,749 --> 00:23:12,915
Steve, you're shivering.

671
00:23:12,983 --> 00:23:14,618
(Steve shivers)

672
00:23:14,685 --> 00:23:17,053
The room's spinning.

673
00:23:17,121 --> 00:23:18,622
Your heart's racing
really fast.

674
00:23:18,689 --> 00:23:20,290
Yeah, I'm cold.
I'm just going into shock.

675
00:23:22,892 --> 00:23:24,660
I'm gonna go try
and get your jacket.

676
00:23:24,727 --> 00:23:25,894
N-no...

677
00:23:25,962 --> 00:23:27,196
Okay,
I want you to look at me.

678
00:23:27,264 --> 00:23:28,531
I want you to look at me.

679
00:23:28,598 --> 00:23:31,400
I want you to keep
talking to me, okay?

680
00:23:31,468 --> 00:23:32,934
I'm an idiot.

681
00:23:33,002 --> 00:23:34,570
You're not.
It's not your fault.

682
00:23:34,638 --> 00:23:38,005
No, I mean, I shouldn't have
waited so long to ask you out.

683
00:23:38,073 --> 00:23:39,474
Let's save the deathbed
confession

684
00:23:39,542 --> 00:23:41,409
for 50 years from now,
okay?

685
00:23:41,477 --> 00:23:43,411
You gonna be there?

686
00:23:44,313 --> 00:23:46,414
(Torch whirs loudly)

687
00:23:46,482 --> 00:23:49,016
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Sam, let us know</i>
<i>when you're close.</i>

688
00:23:49,084 --> 00:23:50,751
Hey, guys,
those threats against Riyaz?

689
00:23:50,819 --> 00:23:52,320
You were right;

690
00:23:52,388 --> 00:23:54,754
the I.P. address traces back
to Davis's group home.

691
00:23:54,822 --> 00:23:57,023
So he did make those threats.

692
00:23:57,091 --> 00:23:59,426
Hey, Ed,
take a look at this one.

693
00:23:59,494 --> 00:24:01,261
Okay, boss,
listen to this.

694
00:24:01,329 --> 00:24:03,197
<i>With one bomb,</i>
<i>you killed 26 people.</i>

695
00:24:03,264 --> 00:24:05,532
<i>Time for you</i>
<i>and your followers</i>

696
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:06,766
<i>to get a taste</i>
<i>of your own medicine.</i>

697
00:24:06,834 --> 00:24:08,034
Taste of his own medicine...

698
00:24:08,102 --> 00:24:09,768
Think Davis built a bomb?

699
00:24:09,836 --> 00:24:11,170
His father mentioned
that he had a degree

700
00:24:11,238 --> 00:24:12,572
in chemical engineering.

701
00:24:12,639 --> 00:24:14,207
So why show up at the restaurant
with a gun?

702
00:24:14,274 --> 00:24:15,941
Maybe he'd already
planted it somewhere;

703
00:24:16,009 --> 00:24:17,643
he wanted to take the leader out
personally.

704
00:24:17,711 --> 00:24:19,645
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Sounds like Riyaz</i>
<i>wasn't his only target.</i>

705
00:24:19,713 --> 00:24:21,380
Okay, boss, we're gonna head
to the group home.

706
00:24:21,448 --> 00:24:23,416
Okay, Eddie, check Davis's room,
check everywhere.

707
00:24:23,483 --> 00:24:25,350
Find out what he's building
and who he's targeting.

708
00:24:25,418 --> 00:24:26,951
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Copy that.</i>

709
00:24:27,019 --> 00:24:27,952
Mr. Fayad?

710
00:24:28,020 --> 00:24:29,087
Riyaz:
Yes, officer?

711
00:24:30,789 --> 00:24:33,391
An officer's gonna take you
downtown for processing.

712
00:24:33,459 --> 00:24:35,126
<i>It's just procedure.</i>

713
00:24:35,194 --> 00:24:36,228
Uh, I'll go with you.

714
00:24:36,295 --> 00:24:37,762
No,

715
00:24:37,830 --> 00:24:40,031
you and Sayid go to the mosque.

716
00:24:40,099 --> 00:24:42,700
Pray for Eric and the others
at the restaurant.

717
00:24:42,767 --> 00:24:44,034
Cashmira:
Okay.

718
00:24:46,037 --> 00:24:49,240
Man:
Come on, let's go.
Come on, come on.

719
00:24:50,174 --> 00:24:51,275
Get back!

720
00:24:51,343 --> 00:24:52,376
Sam, hostages are turning
on him.

721
00:24:52,444 --> 00:24:53,510
Get in there now!

722
00:24:53,578 --> 00:24:54,612
Get back against the wall
now,

723
00:24:54,679 --> 00:24:55,946
or I'll shoot you all
one by one.

724
00:24:56,013 --> 00:24:57,380
Jules:
Drop your weapon.
Drop your weapons.

725
00:24:57,448 --> 00:24:58,448
<i>Drop...</i>

726
00:24:58,515 --> 00:24:59,749
(Glass shatters)

727
00:24:59,816 --> 00:25:01,817
Sam:
Everybody do what the man says!

728
00:25:01,885 --> 00:25:05,054
<i>Drop your weapons</i>
<i>and go back to where you were.</i>

729
00:25:05,122 --> 00:25:06,522
<i>It's all right, buddy,</i>
<i>you can stand down.</i>

730
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:08,625
I got this area of operations
contained.

731
00:25:08,692 --> 00:25:11,060
Go back to where you were, now,
all of you!

732
00:25:11,128 --> 00:25:12,795
<i>Do it now!</i>

733
00:25:12,863 --> 00:25:14,229
Who are you?

734
00:25:14,297 --> 00:25:16,798
Master Corporal Sam Braddock,
Special Forces.

735
00:25:16,866 --> 00:25:18,500
I'm here to help.

736
00:25:19,435 --> 00:25:21,603
You knew this place
was a front for terrorists?

737
00:25:21,671 --> 00:25:22,604
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Sam, don't lie to him.</i>

738
00:25:22,672 --> 00:25:24,539
He's sensitive to deception.

739
00:25:24,607 --> 00:25:25,874
I know what it's like
to feel afraid;

740
00:25:25,941 --> 00:25:28,744
I served two tours
in Afghanistan.

741
00:25:28,811 --> 00:25:30,244
I know what it's like
to walk down the street,

742
00:25:30,312 --> 00:25:32,680
<i>and wonder where they're</i>
<i>gonna strike again.</i>

743
00:25:32,748 --> 00:25:33,914
You feel helpless,

744
00:25:33,982 --> 00:25:35,215
like you're never
gonna be safe.

745
00:25:35,284 --> 00:25:36,717
That's what they want -

746
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:38,586
all of us to live
in a state of fear.

747
00:25:38,654 --> 00:25:41,422
Yeah, that's why we gotta
fight back.

748
00:25:41,490 --> 00:25:42,590
<i>You know that operation</i>
<i>they're-</i>

749
00:25:42,658 --> 00:25:43,791
(gunshot pops,
patrons scream)

750
00:25:43,858 --> 00:25:46,760
Davis and Sam:
(Struggling grunts)

751
00:25:48,562 --> 00:25:49,829
Sam:
Settle down.

752
00:25:49,897 --> 00:25:50,930
Davis:
(Grunts)
What are you doing?!

753
00:25:50,998 --> 00:25:52,332
You lied to me!

754
00:25:53,167 --> 00:25:54,501
You lied to me!

755
00:25:55,269 --> 00:25:56,803
<i>Sam:</i>
<i>I didn't lie.</i>

756
00:25:56,870 --> 00:25:58,104
Subject in custody.

757
00:25:58,172 --> 00:26:00,873
Parker:
Good work, guys.
Good work.

758
00:26:00,941 --> 00:26:02,775
(Breathing hard)

759
00:26:02,842 --> 00:26:03,909
Thank you.

760
00:26:07,180 --> 00:26:09,481
E.M.S.
We need E.M.S. in here now.

761
00:26:16,489 --> 00:26:18,523
Eddie, you find anything
at the group home?

762
00:26:18,590 --> 00:26:21,959
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Boss, we're in the basement.</i>

763
00:26:22,027 --> 00:26:24,462
Davis is building
something here...

764
00:26:24,530 --> 00:26:26,197
(PDA camera clicks)

765
00:26:27,499 --> 00:26:28,700
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>But it doesn't look like</i>
<i>any kind of bomb</i>

766
00:26:28,767 --> 00:26:29,834
<i>I've ever seen.</i>

767
00:26:31,036 --> 00:26:32,102
Have a look.

768
00:26:35,807 --> 00:26:37,941
Those fire extinguishers?

769
00:26:39,844 --> 00:26:41,277
Uh huh.
They're all empty.

770
00:26:41,346 --> 00:26:42,813
Watches, pesticides...

771
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:44,748
What's that on the floor?

772
00:26:44,816 --> 00:26:46,683
(PDA camera clicks)

773
00:26:46,751 --> 00:26:47,684
Castor beans.

774
00:26:47,752 --> 00:26:48,785
Talk to me, Spike.

775
00:26:48,853 --> 00:26:50,052
Castor beans
and pesticides -

776
00:26:50,119 --> 00:26:52,455
major components in both ricin
and sarin.

777
00:26:52,522 --> 00:26:53,789
Nerve gas.

778
00:26:53,857 --> 00:26:55,123
Fire extinguishers
hold compressed gas,

779
00:26:55,191 --> 00:26:56,659
watch is the timer...

780
00:26:56,727 --> 00:26:59,027
He's made a chemical bomb
and it's already out there.

781
00:27:04,821 --> 00:27:05,888
Parker:
Sam?

782
00:27:07,090 --> 00:27:08,490
How is he?

783
00:27:09,125 --> 00:27:10,960
Davis?
Davis, I'm sergeant Parker.

784
00:27:11,027 --> 00:27:13,628
How are you doing?
You doing okay?

785
00:27:13,696 --> 00:27:15,030
Look, I want you to know
that you're safe.

786
00:27:15,098 --> 00:27:16,564
We're not gonna let anything
happen to you.

787
00:27:16,631 --> 00:27:18,099
Okay?

788
00:27:18,167 --> 00:27:20,268
But we could really use
your help right now.

789
00:27:20,336 --> 00:27:22,636
We know that made
some kind of chemical bomb

790
00:27:22,704 --> 00:27:25,639
and we need to know
where it is.

791
00:27:26,608 --> 00:27:27,775
Davis, a bomb like that

792
00:27:27,843 --> 00:27:30,511
could kill a lot
of innocent people.

793
00:27:30,579 --> 00:27:33,646
Sam:
I don't think we're gonna
get anything out of him.

794
00:27:33,714 --> 00:27:36,049
Parker:
Get him to the hospital,
regulate his meds.

795
00:27:36,117 --> 00:27:37,617
Parker:
Keep an eye on Mr. Lagosto.

796
00:27:37,685 --> 00:27:41,020
When he becomes coherent,
you question him again, okay?

797
00:27:41,088 --> 00:27:43,556
Eddie, couldn't get anything.

798
00:27:44,057 --> 00:27:45,525
You need to tear
that place apart

799
00:27:45,593 --> 00:27:47,761
and figure out where
his next target may have been.

800
00:27:47,828 --> 00:27:49,896
Let the social worker, Clive,
know that he's there,

801
00:27:49,963 --> 00:27:51,431
he's safe,

802
00:27:51,499 --> 00:27:52,465
<i>but he's gonna meet us</i>
<i>up at the hospital.</i>

803
00:27:52,533 --> 00:27:54,367
Boss, the social worker's
not here.

804
00:27:54,435 --> 00:27:55,667
Boss, I got something.

805
00:27:55,735 --> 00:27:58,069
All right,
I'm on my way.

806
00:28:02,141 --> 00:28:04,009
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>I'm right here, Steve, okay.</i>
<i>I'm coming with you.</i>

807
00:28:04,076 --> 00:28:05,711
Nah, nah-nah.
You don't have to come with me.

808
00:28:05,779 --> 00:28:07,045
Jules:
You're going into surgery.

809
00:28:07,113 --> 00:28:08,480
You need somebody there
when you wake up.

810
00:28:08,548 --> 00:28:09,948
Yeah, there's a bomb out there;
The team needs you.

811
00:28:10,016 --> 00:28:11,716
Jules: Are you sure?
Steve: Yeah, I'll be all right.

812
00:28:11,784 --> 00:28:13,150
Okay,
I'm gonna come by later.

813
00:28:13,218 --> 00:28:14,351
(Siren wails)

814
00:28:19,792 --> 00:28:21,191
(Gurney rattles)

815
00:28:22,861 --> 00:28:23,861
You better suit up.

816
00:28:23,929 --> 00:28:25,496
<i>Jules:</i>
<i>Yeah.</i>

817
00:28:26,565 --> 00:28:28,932
I got into Davis's computer.
Those threats against Riyaz?

818
00:28:28,999 --> 00:28:30,400
<i>They're in Davis's outbox</i>

819
00:28:30,468 --> 00:28:31,435
<i>but they're not in</i>
<i>his "sent" mail folder.</i>

820
00:28:31,502 --> 00:28:32,769
What does that mean,
Spike?

821
00:28:32,837 --> 00:28:33,503
It means someone was using
his computer

822
00:28:33,571 --> 00:28:34,471
as a proxy server.

823
00:28:34,539 --> 00:28:35,605
Davis didn't send
those threats.

824
00:28:35,673 --> 00:28:36,807
Someone was setting him up.

825
00:28:36,874 --> 00:28:38,308
Can you trace it?

826
00:28:38,375 --> 00:28:39,208
Yeah, I'm running a tunneling
program right now.

827
00:28:40,144 --> 00:28:41,077
(Computer beeps)

828
00:28:41,145 --> 00:28:42,345
Clive Irwin.

829
00:28:42,413 --> 00:28:44,346
His social worker.

830
00:28:44,414 --> 00:28:47,115
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>So why would Clive</i>
<i>want to frame Davis?</i>

831
00:28:47,183 --> 00:28:48,784
Parker: Eddie.
Ed: Boss?

832
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:50,486
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Clive is now a person</i>
<i>of interest.</i>

833
00:28:57,761 --> 00:28:59,627
Wordy, let's get this open.

834
00:28:59,695 --> 00:29:01,262
<i>Wordy:</i>
<i>Copy.</i>

835
00:29:10,806 --> 00:29:12,373
Ed:
Boss, it looks like Clive's
been conducting

836
00:29:12,441 --> 00:29:14,976
his own investigation
of Mr. Fayad.

837
00:29:15,043 --> 00:29:16,343
What'd you find?

838
00:29:16,410 --> 00:29:18,612
We've got articles
on domestic terrorism,

839
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:20,547
surveillance photos
on Mr. Fayad

840
00:29:20,615 --> 00:29:22,048
and other Muslims.

841
00:29:22,116 --> 00:29:23,750
Suspected cell members.

842
00:29:23,818 --> 00:29:25,752
Clive's the one who's paranoid
about terrorism.

843
00:29:25,820 --> 00:29:27,387
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>I think I know why.</i>

844
00:29:27,455 --> 00:29:28,956
<i>Clive's wife was killed</i>
<i>in the London terror attacks</i>

845
00:29:29,023 --> 00:29:30,657
a few years ago.

846
00:29:30,725 --> 00:29:33,125
<i>Carol:</i>
<i>Clive never got over</i>
<i>losing his wife.</i>

847
00:29:33,193 --> 00:29:35,461
Ed:
Did he ever discuss it
with Davis?

848
00:29:35,529 --> 00:29:36,629
It's funny,

849
00:29:36,697 --> 00:29:38,130
he never talked
about it to anyone,

850
00:29:38,198 --> 00:29:41,601
and then a few months ago
they were playing chess...

851
00:29:41,668 --> 00:29:44,604
When the bomb went off,
the train split in half.

852
00:29:45,772 --> 00:29:48,306
She was thrown
onto the tracks.

853
00:29:48,374 --> 00:29:52,176
I tried to go to her,
but I couldn't stand up.

854
00:29:52,244 --> 00:29:54,846
Both my legs were broken.

855
00:29:54,914 --> 00:29:57,382
(Long drawn out inhale)

856
00:29:57,449 --> 00:30:01,252
I didn't know
if she was alive or dead.

857
00:30:02,287 --> 00:30:04,955
Her face was turned away.

858
00:30:06,224 --> 00:30:09,226
I just kept
calling her name.

859
00:30:11,362 --> 00:30:15,032
I'm almost convinced
it's been a bad dream.

860
00:30:19,370 --> 00:30:20,837
(Breathes deeply)

861
00:30:26,209 --> 00:30:29,211
They say that Riyaz Fayad

862
00:30:29,279 --> 00:30:32,649
was connected
to those suicide bombers.

863
00:30:32,716 --> 00:30:35,951
There must be a way
to stop him.

864
00:30:41,357 --> 00:30:45,260
I mean you can't blame Clive
for how he feels.

865
00:30:45,327 --> 00:30:47,228
Okay, thank you.

866
00:30:50,499 --> 00:30:51,266
<i>Did you get all that?</i>

867
00:30:51,333 --> 00:30:52,967
Yeah.

868
00:30:53,035 --> 00:30:54,969
Sounds like Clive's been
whispering in Davis's ear

869
00:30:55,037 --> 00:30:56,236
for months.

870
00:30:56,304 --> 00:30:57,605
Feeding his paranoia
about an attack

871
00:30:57,673 --> 00:30:59,540
and convincing him
to build a bomb.

872
00:30:59,608 --> 00:31:01,075
Well, Davis probably had
no idea

873
00:31:01,142 --> 00:31:02,509
his friend was using him
as a weapon.

874
00:31:02,578 --> 00:31:04,344
Setting him up
to take the fall.

875
00:31:04,412 --> 00:31:05,646
<i>Wordy:</i>
<i>One of the residents</i>
<i>said they saw Clive</i>

876
00:31:05,714 --> 00:31:07,448
driving away 20 minutes ago.

877
00:31:07,515 --> 00:31:08,982
Where'd he go?
No idea.

878
00:31:09,050 --> 00:31:10,617
<i>Just said he's moving fast.</i>

879
00:31:10,685 --> 00:31:12,052
Well, if he was using Davis
to keep his own hands clean,

880
00:31:12,119 --> 00:31:13,519
why would he take the bomb
himself?

881
00:31:13,588 --> 00:31:15,689
'Cause Davis can't now
and the job isn't done.

882
00:31:15,756 --> 00:31:17,523
It's gotta be the mosque.
Remember?

883
00:31:17,592 --> 00:31:19,059
Clive didn't just threaten
Riyaz.

884
00:31:19,126 --> 00:31:20,894
He said, "you and your followers
are gonna get a taste

885
00:31:20,962 --> 00:31:22,195
of your own medicine."

886
00:31:22,262 --> 00:31:23,929
He thinks it's their base
of operations.

887
00:31:23,997 --> 00:31:25,130
Spike:
Lawrence and Avenue Road.

888
00:31:25,198 --> 00:31:26,799
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Let's go, let's move!</i>

889
00:31:26,866 --> 00:31:28,433
(Siren wails)

890
00:31:28,501 --> 00:31:29,802
<i>Clive's car has been spotted</i>
<i>in the parking lot</i>

891
00:31:29,869 --> 00:31:31,604
<i>at the mosque.</i>

892
00:31:33,740 --> 00:31:37,476
(Prayer is being recited
in the prayer room)

893
00:31:50,155 --> 00:31:52,389
(Hushed prayer is recited)

894
00:31:59,964 --> 00:32:01,031
(SUVs rumble up)

895
00:32:09,807 --> 00:32:11,307
Zelovitsky: Sergeant Parker?
Parker: Yeah.

896
00:32:11,375 --> 00:32:13,009
Dr. Zelovitsky,
I'm with Hazmat.

897
00:32:13,076 --> 00:32:14,476
I'm heading up
the medical team.

898
00:32:14,544 --> 00:32:16,211
Any idea what kind of toxin
we're dealing with?

899
00:32:16,279 --> 00:32:17,412
It could be a nerve Agent,

900
00:32:17,480 --> 00:32:19,148
maybe a derivative of ricin
or sarin.

901
00:32:19,215 --> 00:32:20,850
It's hard to be specific
'cause it's a home brew.

902
00:32:20,917 --> 00:32:22,417
We need to prepare
for hemorrhaging,

903
00:32:22,485 --> 00:32:24,219
convulsions,
even fatalities.

904
00:32:24,287 --> 00:32:25,688
Let's hope
it doesn't come to that.

905
00:32:25,756 --> 00:32:27,556
Zelovitsky: We'll be ready.
Parker: Thank you.

906
00:32:27,624 --> 00:32:29,357
Ed:
Okay, Spike,
what do we got?

907
00:32:29,424 --> 00:32:31,126
Looks like Davis outfitted
the extinguishers

908
00:32:31,193 --> 00:32:32,193
with artificial heads.

909
00:32:32,261 --> 00:32:33,461
He presses
a manual detonator,

910
00:32:33,529 --> 00:32:35,429
the cylinder will blow
releasing the gas.

911
00:32:35,497 --> 00:32:36,731
Okay, can you disarm it?

912
00:32:36,799 --> 00:32:38,199
Spike:
Yeah, if we find it in time.

913
00:32:38,267 --> 00:32:39,134
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>If we evacuate,</i>
<i>it'll tip him off.</i>

914
00:32:39,201 --> 00:32:40,301
He could release the toxin.

915
00:32:40,369 --> 00:32:42,370
Okay, absolute stealth,
guys.

916
00:32:42,437 --> 00:32:43,804
Spike, wordy,
you take the back.

917
00:32:43,872 --> 00:32:45,605
Sam and Jules, west.
Boss, let's take the east.

918
00:32:45,674 --> 00:32:46,907
Let's move it.

919
00:32:56,818 --> 00:32:58,886
<i>Cashmira:</i>
<i>Okay, babe.</i>
<i>You go ahead.</i>

920
00:32:58,953 --> 00:33:00,753
Mommy will be right over,
okay?

921
00:33:03,390 --> 00:33:05,524
(Imam continues leading
the prayer session)

922
00:33:05,592 --> 00:33:07,894
(Whispered response)

923
00:33:11,765 --> 00:33:14,767
<i>Cashmira:</i>
<i>Uh, can I help you?</i>

924
00:33:18,237 --> 00:33:19,204
Can I help you?

925
00:33:19,271 --> 00:33:21,673
(Imam prays)

926
00:33:25,178 --> 00:33:26,244
Masks on.

927
00:33:31,917 --> 00:33:33,650
(Door pops open)

928
00:33:49,433 --> 00:33:51,768
<i>Sam:</i>
<i>I have a visual.</i>

929
00:33:51,836 --> 00:33:53,103
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>Where?</i>

930
00:33:53,170 --> 00:33:54,637
Looks like the prayer room.

931
00:33:54,705 --> 00:33:55,905
Ed:
Does he have the bomb?

932
00:33:55,973 --> 00:33:57,473
Affirmative.
I have the solution.

933
00:33:57,541 --> 00:33:59,142
<i>Spike:</i>
<i>Sam, hold fire.</i>

934
00:33:59,210 --> 00:34:00,676
If the bomb hits the floor,
it'll blow.

935
00:34:00,745 --> 00:34:02,712
Ed:
Spike, shut down
the ventilation system.

936
00:34:02,780 --> 00:34:04,947
If the toxin's released,
we can keep it contained.

937
00:34:05,014 --> 00:34:05,914
Copy that.

938
00:34:06,916 --> 00:34:08,316
I'm going on in.

939
00:34:12,756 --> 00:34:13,756
Ed:
Police!

940
00:34:14,224 --> 00:34:15,257
(Frightened murmurs)

941
00:34:15,324 --> 00:34:17,359
Team:
Police! SRU! Police!

942
00:34:18,361 --> 00:34:20,427
Ed:
Right there!
Everybody exit the building.

943
00:34:20,495 --> 00:34:21,996
<i>Everyone exit the building</i>
<i>now!</i>

944
00:34:22,064 --> 00:34:24,531
Exit the room now,
do it now!

945
00:34:26,268 --> 00:34:27,635
Nobody move.

946
00:34:27,702 --> 00:34:30,671
<i>Or I'll set off this bomb</i>
<i>right now!</i>

947
00:34:31,606 --> 00:34:34,675
Parker:
Clive, just put it down.

948
00:34:34,743 --> 00:34:37,210
Put it down,
and move away slowly.

949
00:34:37,278 --> 00:34:39,712
I don't expect you
to believe me.

950
00:34:39,781 --> 00:34:41,614
Someone has to stop them.

951
00:34:41,682 --> 00:34:44,317
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>But will you just listen</i>
<i>closely to what I have to say</i>

952
00:34:44,385 --> 00:34:47,120
before you do anything
that you might regret here.

953
00:34:47,188 --> 00:34:49,756
<i>ATU -</i>
<i>anti-terrorist unit -</i>

954
00:34:49,824 --> 00:34:53,325
<i>fully investigated Riyaz Fayad</i>
<i>and the others of this mosque,</i>

955
00:34:53,393 --> 00:34:54,827
<i>and they've been cleared.</i>

956
00:34:54,895 --> 00:34:56,762
No they haven't!

957
00:34:56,830 --> 00:34:58,264
Don't play games with me.

958
00:34:58,331 --> 00:34:59,598
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>They have.</i>

959
00:34:59,666 --> 00:35:01,033
None of them have links
to the terrorists

960
00:35:01,101 --> 00:35:03,602
that were responsible
for your wife's death.

961
00:35:03,670 --> 00:35:04,670
<i>Clive, you push that button</i>

962
00:35:04,737 --> 00:35:06,105
<i>and you're gonna die here.</i>

963
00:35:06,173 --> 00:35:07,906
Is that what you really want?

964
00:35:10,142 --> 00:35:12,710
Is that what Laura
would want?

965
00:35:15,714 --> 00:35:16,848
(Inhales shakily)

966
00:35:17,783 --> 00:35:19,017
If that's what it takes.

967
00:35:19,084 --> 00:35:20,685
Put it down.

968
00:35:22,554 --> 00:35:24,087
Clive!

969
00:35:24,155 --> 00:35:26,824
(Detonator clicks, gas hisses,
people cry out, panicked)

970
00:35:26,891 --> 00:35:28,058
Ed:
Everybody get down
on the ground!

971
00:35:28,126 --> 00:35:30,760
(Bomb explodes,
terrified screams)

972
00:35:34,677 --> 00:35:36,310
Everybody out now!

973
00:35:36,378 --> 00:35:37,578
Wordy:
Okay, through the doors
as quickly as you can!

974
00:35:37,645 --> 00:35:38,812
<i>Cashmira:</i>
<i>Sayid?!</i>

975
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:39,947
<i>Sayid?!</i>

976
00:35:40,748 --> 00:35:41,915
<i>Sayid?!</i>

977
00:35:42,351 --> 00:35:45,252
Please wait,
I have to find Sayid.

978
00:35:46,821 --> 00:35:48,489
Clive:
Ungh!

979
00:35:48,556 --> 00:35:50,524
<i>Wordy:</i>
<i>Everybody, out, out!</i>
<i>Go, go, go, go!</i>

980
00:35:50,592 --> 00:35:51,725
Sayid:
(Crying)

981
00:35:51,793 --> 00:35:53,159
<i>Wordy:</i>
<i>Move it, move it!</i>

982
00:35:53,227 --> 00:35:55,561
Ed:
Wordy, we gotta get to Sayid.
Let's go!

983
00:35:55,629 --> 00:35:58,198
(Cacophony of hurried chatter)

984
00:35:58,799 --> 00:36:00,433
We need these people contained.

985
00:36:00,501 --> 00:36:02,002
Everyone needs
to be sprayed down,

986
00:36:02,069 --> 00:36:03,603
that includes you!

987
00:36:03,670 --> 00:36:05,372
Ed:
I hear ya, doc.
As soon as everyone's safe.

988
00:36:05,439 --> 00:36:07,073
Zelovitsky:
Straight over to the blue tent.
Watch your step.

989
00:36:07,141 --> 00:36:08,907
People will be there
to help you.

990
00:36:08,975 --> 00:36:10,109
Wordy:
Keep going, keep going!

991
00:36:10,176 --> 00:36:12,344
Ed:
Go! Go! Let's go!

992
00:36:12,412 --> 00:36:13,879
Get outta here!

993
00:36:13,946 --> 00:36:15,747
(Overlapping chatter)

994
00:36:19,519 --> 00:36:20,785
<i>Parker:</i>
<i>All right, team one,</i>

995
00:36:20,853 --> 00:36:22,854
<i>full sweep</i>
<i>for anyone left inside.</i>

996
00:36:22,922 --> 00:36:24,255
Sayid!

997
00:36:24,323 --> 00:36:25,856
<i>Sayid!</i>

998
00:36:25,924 --> 00:36:27,325
<i>Sayid!</i>

999
00:36:27,393 --> 00:36:28,459
Come on.

1000
00:36:28,527 --> 00:36:29,894
I got ya, I got ya.
Come on.

1001
00:36:29,961 --> 00:36:31,362
Wordy:
Let's go.

1002
00:36:37,536 --> 00:36:39,504
We need some help!
Let's go!

1003
00:36:39,571 --> 00:36:41,371
Let's go, right here!
Come on!

1004
00:36:41,439 --> 00:36:42,839
Cashmira:
Oh my God, Sayid!

1005
00:36:42,907 --> 00:36:44,741
Ed:
It's okay.
Doc!

1006
00:36:44,808 --> 00:36:47,044
<i>Cashmira:</i>
<i>Is he gonna be okay?</i>

1007
00:36:47,111 --> 00:36:47,911
Baby!

1008
00:36:47,978 --> 00:36:49,179
Resps are shallow.

1009
00:36:49,247 --> 00:36:50,914
I need five milligrams
of atropine.

1010
00:36:50,981 --> 00:36:53,016
Ed:
They're gonna do everything
they can.

1011
00:36:53,084 --> 00:36:54,384
Cashmira:
Sayid, baby,
mommy's right here.

1012
00:36:54,452 --> 00:36:55,752
Come on, come on,
let's go!

1013
00:37:27,349 --> 00:37:28,315
<i>Ed:</i>
<i>Finished my report.</i>

1014
00:37:28,383 --> 00:37:29,483
Parker:
Thanks, buddy.

1015
00:37:31,686 --> 00:37:33,653
I hear you made a call
on Riyaz's behalf.

1016
00:37:33,721 --> 00:37:35,055
Yeah.

1017
00:37:35,123 --> 00:37:37,424
Boss, he only threatened us
because he was scared.

1018
00:37:37,492 --> 00:37:38,992
He thought we were
the rendition squad.

1019
00:37:39,060 --> 00:37:41,661
He saw what he feared
the most.

1020
00:37:41,729 --> 00:37:42,996
And he wasn't
the only one today

1021
00:37:43,064 --> 00:37:46,232
who something
that wasn't there.

1022
00:37:46,300 --> 00:37:48,434
Spike:
Hey, update from the hospital.

1023
00:37:48,502 --> 00:37:50,002
Five people still in serious
condition,

1024
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:51,737
<i>but they're expected</i>
<i>to pull through.</i>

1025
00:37:51,805 --> 00:37:53,806
What about the boy - Sayid?

1026
00:37:53,873 --> 00:37:54,940
Doing okay.

1027
00:37:55,875 --> 00:37:57,143
Thanks, Spike.

1028
00:37:57,211 --> 00:37:58,277
Yeah.

1029
00:38:02,081 --> 00:38:09,621
♪

1030
00:38:09,622 --> 00:38:17,027
♪

1031
